{"experiment_id": "synthetic_benign", "epoch": 5, "role": "user", "artifact_class": "PullRequest", "identifier": ["microsoft", "vscode", 6], "url": "https://github.com/microsoft/vscode/pull/6", "semantic_text": "When Firebase fails to initialize (often due to restrictive security rules or network issues), the `websocket-client.js` would fall back to a local simulation mode, logging a generic \"Firebase\u4e0d\u53ef\u7528\" message.\n\nThis commit updates the console message in `js/websocket-client.js` to be a more informative warning. It now explicitly advises you to check the browser console for earlier, more detailed error messages that might have been logged by `firebase-config.js` or `firebase-battle.js`. These earlier messages often contain specific reasons for the failure, such as permission denied errors from security rules or network connectivity problems.\n\nThis change aims to make debugging Firebase setup issues more straightforward.", "semantic_meaning": null, "semantic_ref": null, "semantic_label": "benign", "semantic_content_type": "real", "timestamp": 1604846005.0}
